The White House held a press briefing to discuss President Obama's upcoming trip to South Korea for the Nuclear Security Summit. The officials discussed the schedule, purpose of the summit, and bilateral meetings with other leaders. The President will visit the demilitarized zone, meet with Prime Minister Erdogan of Turkey, have a bilateral meeting with President Lee of South Korea, give a speech at Hankuk University, and have bilateral meetings with President Medvedev of Russia and President Hu Jintao of China. The officials also discussed the progress made in securing nuclear materials and the ongoing efforts to prevent nuclear terrorism.